column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Lake level has been going down slowly since May.  I listed as normal previously but has been receding slightly each month.
Water level: Up about 1" from last check
Lake getting colder-little boat traffic-cleared up a lot.
Ice off on April 27.  Very cold- 25 degrees in the morning.
Heavy motor boat traffic which stripped things up.
Beautiful clear day!  Water warmed up nicely for swimming.
Recent rain raised lake level slightly.
Weather clear.  There is a slight murkiness in the water.
Clear day- the water is slightly cloudy.
Weather clear and there is no motor boat activity.
Ice - off = April 19th- weather - cloudy and windy.
Weather clear- water still too cold for swimming.
Weather hazy with some sunshine- slight breeze.
Clear day- slight breeze from S.
Weather cloudy- slight breeze from southwest.
Heavy jet ski activity yesterday and day before- water murky.
Some clouds- reading taken when cloudy.
Clear day but water had a brownish cast to it.
Cloudy day and water still has a brownish cast to it.
Clear day though the water still has a bit of a brownish cast.
Cloudy day and water still has a brownish cast to it- somewhat murky.
Cloudy- water appears to be clearing up and losing its brownish cast.
Clear- windy. ice over 11/21- then ice out. Ice over 12/9- then ice out. 12/19 ice over for good.
Ice out April 6- 1999.  Water temperature is 50 degrees F.  Took water sample for chemistry analysis - Steven's Point.
Water temperature is 58 degrees F.  Clear and calm day.
Water temperature is 60 degrees F. Cloudy. Slight breeze from NE.
Water temperature 61 degrees F.  Partly cloudy.  Quite rainy for past 2 weeks.
The water temperature is 72 degrees F.
The water temperature is 73 degrees F. Sunny.  Slight breeze from SW.
The water temperature is 73 degrees F.  Hazy.  Slight breeze from SE.
The water temperature is 76 degrees F.  Partly cloudy.  Slight breeze.
The water temperature is 78 degrees F. Partly cloudy. Slight breeze from N.
The water temperature is 83 degrees F. Hazy. Light breeze from SW.
The water temperature is 83 degrees F. Clear. Wind out of SW.
The water temperature is 76 degrees F. Hazy. Wind from SW.
The water temperature is 75 degrees F. Clear. Wind from SW.
The water temperature is 79 degrees F. Hazy. Wind from SW.
The water temperature is 63 degrees. F. Some clouds but sunny.  Slight breeze from SE.
The water temperature is 63 degrees F. Sunny.  Slight breeze from SW.  Lake very clear.  Could see disk disappear into muck.
The water temperature is 51 degrees F. Sunny.  Wind from NW.  Lake very clear.
lots of pollen lake quite murkey
water very clear light wind- very low level of pollen
have had over 6 inches of reai in last week water at a level higher that after spring thaw - more sediment along shore than usual
nice day- water still on the high side we had a lot of
sunny day- slight chop- appears that weeds are
sunny no wind lake looks good
Clear- hot (82) + humid. Lake level the lowest I'm seen in 15 years.
Sunny- 60 degrees- eagle feeding young- loon nesting- geese on nest.
Clear- bluebird day. Glassy conditions- some tree pollen on the surface. One other boat on lake.
